@node FIAlloc "FileID.library/FIAllocFileInfo"

        NAME
                FIAllocFileInfo    -- Create a FI_FileInfo structure.

        SYNOPSIS
                FIAllocFileInfo (void)

                struct FI_FileInfo * FIAllocFileInfo (void)

        FUNCTION
                Allocates & initializes an FI_FileInfo structure to store all
                identification information about a file. This structure must
                be allocated once before identifying files.

        RESULT
                FileInfo     - (struct FI_FileInfo *). A pointer to the allocated
                               structure or NULL if out of memory. This structure
                               must be freed using @{"FIFreeFileInfo()" link "FIFree"}.

        SEE ALSO
                @{"FIFreeFileInfo()" link "FIFree"}
@endnode
@node FIFree "FileID.library/FIFreeFileInfo"

        NAME
                FIFreeFileInfo    -- Free a FI_FileInfo structure.

        SYNOPSIS
                FIFreeFileInfo (FileInfo)
                                   A1

                void FIFreeFileInfo (struct FI_FileInfo *)

        FUNCTION
                Frees an FI_FileInfo structure back to memory.

        INPUTS
                FileInfo        - A FIFileInfo structure as allocated with
                                  @{"FIAllocFileInfo()" link "FIAlloc"}

        SEE ALSO
                @{"FIAllocFileInfo()" link "FIAlloc"}
@endnode
@node FIID "FileID.library/FIIdentify"

        NAME
                FIIdentify     -- Identify a file type

        SYNOPSIS
                FIIdentify (Address, FileInfo)
                              A0        A1

                void FIIdentify (APTR, struct FI_FileInfo *)

        FUNCTION
                Examines a file already loaded into memory. Only the first
                1200 bytes are used therefor.

        INPUTS
                Address      - The start address of a file already read
                               into memory. This address *MUST* be even.
                               For a complete file analysis, the first 1200
                               bytes are analyzed. If the file is smaller
                               than 1200 bytes, fill up the buffer with
                               null-bytes to avoid wrong results !

                FileInfo     - An FI_FileInfo structure, allocated using
                               @{"FIAllocFileInfo()" link "FIAlloc"}.

                               This structure gets filled with all available
                               information. Beyond that, this function does
                               not return a Result.

        NOTES
                Assembler programmers note that this function preserves A1.

        SEE ALSO
                @{"FIAllocFileInfo()" link "FIAlloc"}, @{"FIIdentifyFromName()" link "FIIDName"}
@endnode
@node FIIDName "FileID.library/FIIdentifyFromName"

        NAME
                FIIdentifyFromName    -- Identify a file type

        SYNOPSIS
                FIIdentifyFromName (FileInfo, Name)
                                       A1      D1

                long FIIdentifyFromName (struct FI_FileInfo *, STRPTR)

        FUNCTION
                Identifies a file by file name. Don't mischange this:
                the name itself doesn't get analyzed anyway. This function
                opens the file, reads the first 1200 bytes (the whole file
                if smaller) and then tries to identify it.

        INPUTS
                FileInfo     - An FI_FileInfo structure, allocated using
                               @{"FIAllocFileInfo()" link "FIAlloc"}.

                               This structure gets filled with all available
                               information.

                Name         - A standard AmigaDOS file name.

        RESULT
                Error        - NULL if everything went ok. The passed FI_FileInfo
                               structure will then be filled. If an error occured,
                               FI_FileInfo->FI_Description points to an error text
                               instead of a file description.

        NOTES
                Assembler programmers note that this function preserves A1.

        SEE ALSO
                @{"FIAllocFileInfo()" link "FIAlloc"}, @{"FIIdentify()" link "FIID"}
@endnode
@node FIGetHighID "FileID.library/FIGetHighID"

        NAME
                FIGetHighID - Get the highest FileID number currently defined.

        SYNOPSIS
                FIGetHighID (void)

                long FIGetHighID (void)

        FUNCTION
                Returns the highest file ID number supported by the
                currently installed FileID.library version.

        RESULT
                HighID   (long).

        NOTES
                Assembler programmers note that this function preserves all
                CPU registers except D0.

        SEE ALSO
                @{"FIGetIDString()" link "FIGetIDString"}
@endnode
@node FIGetIDString "FileID.library/FIGetIDString"

        NAME
                FIGetIDString    -- Get a specific FileID string.

        SYNOPSIS
                FIGetIDString (IDNumber)
                                  D0

                STRPTR FIGetIDString (long)

        INPUTS
                IDNumber   - Any file type number, as defined in
                             include:libraries/FileID.h.

        FUNCTION
                Returns the FI_Description string belonging to the given
                ID number.

        RESULT
                String     - (STRPTR). The description string or NULL if the
                             given number was out of range.

        SEE ALSO
                @{"FIGetHighID()" link "FIGetHighID"}
@endnode

@node Notes "FileID.Guide: Notes"

Don't open FileID.library with VERSION_ANY or VERSION == 1, because V 1.0
includes a serious bug ! Always request a library version >= 2.

The maximum length of a file description string equals 35 bytes.

You may re-use an FI_FileInfo structure as often as you want. If you want
to examine lots of files, you don't have to FIAllocFileInfo() for every
single file.

The FI_FileInfo structure is read-only. Do not modify.

Don't misunderstand @{"FIIdentifyFromName()" link "FIIDName"}. Currently, this function checks
only the file contents. The filename itself is not examined for any
extensions, making assumptions about what the file might be. This is much
too unsure.

Note that FIIdentifyFromName() was made for easy single file analysis.
If you wish to examine lots of files, you can save some time when managing
file I/O yourself and then using FIIdentify(), because FIIdentifyFromName()
must allocate and deallocate the needed memory for every single file.
@endnode
